Ideas that'll transform the future of mankind.

333
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:26,500
在叙利亚首都大马士革
Damascus, Syria.

334
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:29,430
耶稣被钉死在十字架上的四年之后
Four years after the crucifixion.

335
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:32,000
有一个人正在逃亡路上
A man is on the run.

336
00:30:32,010 --> 00:30:34,140
他就是保罗
Paul.

337
00:30:36,220 --> 00:30:38,720
一名传道者 一个闹事者
Preacher, troublemaker,

338
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:44,260
也是基督教历史中最重要的皈依者
And the most important convert in the story of christianity.

339
00:30:44,260 --> 00:30:47,400
在他还未信奉基督教 逃亡大马士革的路上
Before his conversion on the road to Damascus,

340
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:50,970
他曾迫害过基督徒
He persecuted christians.

341
00:30:50,970 --> 00:30:54,440
但现在 他将让一个无关紧要的教派
But now he will turn an insignificant sect

342
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:57,840
变成一种世界性的宗教
Into a world religion.

343
00:30:57,840 --> 00:31:02,080
今天 人们尊称他为圣徒保罗
Today, he's known as Saint Paul.

344
00:31:03,380 --> 00:31:05,550
他激情四射
He was a passionate guy,

345
00:31:05,550 --> 00:31:07,350
他勇气过人
he was a guy with grit.

346
00:31:07,350 --> 00:31:09,490
他虔诚地信仰着自己的上帝
He really believed in his God,

347
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:11,050
真心相信他的福音
really believed in his gospel,

348
00:31:11,060 --> 00:31:16,730
诚心相信基督是唯一的救赎
really believed that Christ was the only way.

349
00:31:16,730 --> 00:31:20,200
为了传播基督就是弥赛亚(救世主)的讯息
For spreading the message that Christ is the Messiah,

350
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:25,130
保罗被通缉了
Paul is a wanted man.

351
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:28,700
对犹太统治者来说 他是个异教徒
To Jewish leaders, he's a heretic.

352
00:31:28,710 --> 00:31:34,180
对罗马人来说 他是个煽动者
To the Romans, a rabble-rouser.

353
00:31:34,180 --> 00:31:38,000
如果被捕 他将被处以极刑
If caught, he'll be executed.

354
00:31:42,180 --> 00:31:45,150
大马士革是一座石墙包围的城池
Damascus is a walled city.

355
00:31:45,150 --> 00:31:48,400
每个门都有重兵把守
Every gate is heavily guarded.

356
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:02,530
保罗的逃亡路线...
Paul's escape route...

357
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:05,760
便是越墙而过
Over the walls.

358
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:21,420
接下来的二十年里 保罗游历了罗马帝国
For twenty years, Paul travels the Roman Empire

359
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:24,380
他和其他的信徒们相互联系
Contacting other believers,

360
00:32:25,820 --> 00:32:28,290
传递着希望之音
Spreading a message of hope.

361
00:32:28,290 --> 00:32:30,030
他告诉人们
He's telling people,

362
00:32:30,030 --> 00:32:35,930
"基督教能让人获得救赎
"Christianity creates a salvation for anyone.

363
00:32:35,930 --> 00:32:39,400
"如果有个奴隶 一直被其主人虐待
"If you have a slave who's being abused by his master,

364
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:42,000
"此生悲惨万分 那在来世
"Who has a horrible life, in the next life,

365
00:32:42,010 --> 00:32:43,540
"他的主人会得到应有的报应
"His master will get what he deserves

366
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:45,270
"至于这个奴隶 如果他是个好人
"And the slave, if he's a good man,

367
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:47,340
"相信基督耶稣并视之为其上帝和救世主
"Who accepts Jesus Christ as his lord and savior

368
00:32:47,350 --> 00:32:51,110
"在来世 他就会得到好报
"Will get what he deserves."

369
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:57,350
保罗给整个帝国的基督信徒们写了信函
Paul writes letters to fellow Christians around the empire:

370
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:02,720
有罗马书 帖撒罗尼迦书 格林多书（圣经新约 保罗所著）
Romans, thessalonians and corinthians.

371
00:33:02,730 --> 00:33:07,260
它们几乎占了圣经新约全书中的一半
They make up nearly half of the new testament.

372
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,620
"世间再无犹太人和希腊人之异
"There is no longer Jew or Greek,

373
00:33:10,630 --> 00:33:13,490
"奴隶和自由之身之差 男女之别
"Slave or free, male and female,

374
00:33:13,500 --> 00:33:15,900
"因你们都存在于基督耶稣之下
"For all of you are one in Jesus Christ.

375
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:20,530
"我们这儿的许多人 在基督里同为一体
"We who are many are one body in Christ.

376
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:22,540
"爱是恒久忍耐 是温润善良
"Love is patient and kind,

377
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:25,710
"爱是不嫉妒 自负 傲慢或粗鲁..."
"Love is not jealous or boastful, arrogant or rude..."

378
00:33:25,710 --> 00:33:28,880
这些信件就像我们在阿拉伯之春运动中
Those letters become very much like the Twitter tweets

379
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:32,280
看到的Twitter网一样
that we see during the Arab Spring.

380
00:33:33,340 --> 00:33:35,910
这就是当时的交流方式
This was the communication of the time

381
00:33:35,910 --> 00:33:39,050
但多数是在罗马的监控之下
and it was very much under the Roman radar.

382
00:33:40,950 --> 00:33:43,620
"我作孩子时 话语像孩子
"When I was a child, I talked like a child,

383
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:46,790
"思绪像孩子 意念像孩子..."
"I thought like a child, I reasoned as a child..."

384
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:50,360
保罗将这些信件授与其他信徒
Paul's letters are entrusted to other believers

385
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:53,590
他们将此传遍罗马帝国
Who deliver them across the empire.

386
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:58,960
"但当我长大成人 便将孩童之事丢弃"
"But when I became a man, I put away childish things."

387
00:34:00,860 --> 00:34:03,330
在这个时候 罗马已经修建了
By this time, Rome has built

388
00:34:03,330 --> 00:34:06,200
二十五万英里的公路
A quarter of a million miles of roads,

389
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:10,700
这些路足够绕地球十圈
Enough to circle the earth ten times.

390
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:15,840
有着连接二百五十个重要港口的航道
Shipping lanes connect 250 major ports.

391
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:20,840
这就是保罗传播信息的方法
This is how Paul spreads the word.

392
00:34:26,610 --> 00:34:30,720
''信仰 希望与爱三者相伴
"So Faith, Hope and Love abide, these three.

393
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:34,450
"但最重要的是爱"
"But the greatest of these is Love."

394
00:34:35,150 --> 00:34:38,020
早期基督教的故事证明了
The story of early Christianity really speaks

395
00:34:38,020 --> 00:34:40,760
思想的力量
to the power of ideas,

396
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:43,260
是思想创造了历史
that is what creates history,

397
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:45,230
改变了人民
that's what changes people,

398
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:46,830
造就了文明
that's what makes civilization.

399
00:34:46,830 --> 00:34:50,000
这一切都始于思想
It's ideas, it always starts with ideas.

400
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:03,940
150年后 在罗马帝国的一个重要港口
150 years later, on the outskirts of Carthage,

401
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:06,920
迦太基的城郊外
One of the largest ports in the Roman Empire,

402
00:35:08,110 --> 00:35:11,020
常有一群基督教徒们偷偷地会面
A group of Christians meet in secret.

403
00:35:13,580 --> 00:35:16,990
私人民房当做教堂
Private houses double up as churches.

404
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:22,460
早期的基督教只是
Early Christianity was a religious movement

405
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:24,660
穷困潦倒之人
for the extremely poor,

406
00:35:24,660 --> 00:35:26,430
奴隶们
for the slaves,

407
00:35:26,430 --> 00:35:28,330
还有女人们参与的宗教运动
and for many women.

408
00:35:28,330 --> 00:35:32,500
基本上 任何在罗马社会没有发言权的人
Basically anyone who didn't have a voice in Roman society

409
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:37,040
都能在基督教的运动中畅所欲言
could find a voice in the Christian movement.

410
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:42,340
在罗马法律上 全国有八百万奴隶
Across the empire, 8 million people are slaves

411
00:35:42,350 --> 00:35:46,150
不享有任何权利
With no rights in Roman Law.

412
00:35:46,150 --> 00:35:53,320
三千万妇女无投票权和担任公职的权利
30 million are women who can't vote or hold public office.

413
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:58,730
在她们当中有个女孩叫佩尔培图阿
Among them, Perpetua.

414
00:35:58,730 --> 00:36:03,760
二十二岁初为人母 颠覆叛逆
22 years old, a new mother, and a subversive.

415
00:36:07,220 --> 00:36:09,780
一年前政府下令
A year earlier, an imperial decree

416
00:36:09,790 --> 00:36:14,450
将基督教定为非法教会
Made conversion to Christianity illegal.

417
00:36:14,460 --> 00:36:20,120
像佩尔培图阿这种皈依者则成为了国家的敌人
Converts like Perpetua are now enemies of the state.

418
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:28,440
他们的罪行是 拒绝敬拜罗马神灵
Their crime: refusing to honor the Roman Gods.

419
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:33,770
你得有点疯狂才能成为基督徒
You had to be a little bit crazy to be a Christian,

420
00:36:33,770 --> 00:36:36,670
而这足以让你被处以死刑
it was enough to get you killed,

421
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:38,810
因为你只忠于
because you were saying your allegiance was

422
00:36:38,810 --> 00:36:41,810
耶稣还有他的父亲
to Christ and to his father

423
00:36:41,820 --> 00:36:45,180
而并未忠于帝国
and not to the emperor.

424
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:47,190
你会不停地回头看看身后
You would've been always looking over your shoulder,

425
00:36:47,190 --> 00:36:49,650
害怕有人跟踪
like, is someone following me

426
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:52,720
或者害怕有人知道自己是基督教徒
or does someone know I'm a Christian.

427
00:36:52,730 --> 00:36:59,040
你会偏执多疑 不敢对人敞开心扉
You would've been paranoid, afraid to talk to anyone openly.

428
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:06,420
帝国的地下警察 也称弗鲁曼塔里
The empire's secret police: the Frumentarii.

429
00:37:10,610 --> 00:37:14,560
他们利用眼线来抓捕异端分子
They use a network of informers to hunt down dissidents.

430
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:50,920
佩尔培图阿被指控为叛国
Perpetua is charged with treason.

431
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:58,200
被关进监狱的她等候着残酷命运的到来
She's sent to prison to await her fate.

432
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:10,290
她喜欢写日记
She keeps a diary,

433
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:12,830
现存最早的文字
The earliest words that still survive

434
00:38:12,830 --> 00:38:16,330
是由一位基督教妇女写下的:
Written by a Christian woman:

435
00:38:16,330 --> 00:38:23,710
"和我斗争的并不是野兽 而是邪恶
"I am not to fight with beasts but against the devil.

436
00:38:23,710 --> 00:38:29,710
"我知道胜利的曙光已经不远了!"
"And I know that victory is waiting for me!"

437
00:38:30,610 --> 00:38:34,720
信徒们的终极考验...
The ultimate test for any believer...

438
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:37,630
就是为你的信仰而死
To die for your faith.

439
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:50,830
基督教徒佩尔培图阿即将面对
Christian dissident Perpetua faces a horrible death

440
00:38:50,830 --> 00:38:54,300
迦太基竞技场上残酷的死刑
In the arena at Carthage.

441
00:39:00,390 --> 00:39:03,860
基督教徒们会被扔向猛兽
Christians are thrown to wild animals,

442
00:39:03,860 --> 00:39:07,300
或全身涂上焦油活埋
Or covered in tar and burned alive,

443
00:39:07,300 --> 00:39:09,460
或者是砍头
Or beheaded.

444
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:15,200
不过只要佩尔培图阿能够主动信仰罗马教神
But Perpetua can still save herself

445
00:39:15,210 --> 00:39:19,110
她仍然有一线希望活下来
If she makes an offering to the Roman Gods.

446
00:39:19,110 --> 00:39:21,380
罗马人会跟这类人说
The Romans come to these people and they say,

447
00:39:21,380 --> 00:39:23,210
"瞧你给我们惹出的麻烦
"Look you're stirring up trouble for us.

448
00:39:23,210 --> 00:39:25,410
"你公开声明
"Make some public declaration

449
00:39:25,420 --> 00:39:30,090
"说你没有反对这个国家
"That says you're not against the state.

450
00:39:30,090 --> 00:39:32,550
"承认罗马帝国就是你所敬重的神
"Admit that the emperor is a god,

451
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:35,960
"你就能安然无恙"
"And that'll show that you are okay."

452
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:43,630
佩尔培图阿的家人前往监狱探望
Perpetua's family visits her in prison.

453
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:46,200
让她哺育自己的孩子
She's allowed to nurse her baby.

454
00:39:50,310 --> 00:39:52,570
她的父亲乞求她回心转意
Her father pleads with her to back down

455
00:39:52,580 --> 00:39:54,900
接受罗马人的条件
And accept the Roman rules.

456
00:39:58,210 --> 00:40:01,920
他说: "孩子 想想我吧"
"Daughter,' he said, 'have pity on me,

457
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:04,050
"别丢下我
"do not abandon me,

458
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:09,060
"想想你的孩子吧 放弃你的自尊吧!"
"have pity on your baby, give up your pride!"

459
00:40:09,060 --> 00:40:11,860
"我尽力安慰他 对他说
"I tried to comfort him, saying,

460
00:40:11,860 --> 00:40:16,900
"事事均会依上帝之愿发生"
"It will happen as God wills."

461
00:40:16,900 --> 00:40:19,300
真正的基督教徒不能抨击自己的宗教
A real Christian can't denounce their religion,

462
00:40:19,300 --> 00:40:21,200
无论是公开场合还是私下
they can't do it in public, they can't do it in private,

463
00:40:21,200 --> 00:40:23,440
即使在心里也不能这样做
they can't do it in their heart,

464
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:28,860
如果做了就会在地狱中永受煎熬 这就是信仰
because they will burn in hell forever, that's the belief.

465
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:39,350
可以想象这需要多大的勇气
Imagine how profoundly courageous one had to be,

466
00:40:39,350 --> 00:40:41,490
将生死置之度外 然后骄傲地说
to put your life on the line and say,

467
00:40:41,490 --> 00:40:48,000
"是的 我是一名基督教徒"
"Yes, I am a follower of Jesus the Christ."

468
00:40:50,830 --> 00:40:53,200
这样做需要的勇气 这样简单的行为
The courage to do that, that simple act,

469
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:57,860
足以说明信仰的力量
speaks volumes about the power of faith.

470
00:41:07,780 --> 00:41:09,910
根据她日记的记载
According to her diary,

471
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:13,080
佩尔培图阿自愿接受死刑
Perpetua goes willingly to her death.

472
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:21,090
她的勇气感动了一名监狱看守
Her courage inspires one of the prison guards,

473
00:41:21,090 --> 00:41:25,680
他叫布田 之后他也加入了基督教
A man called Pudens, to convert.

474
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:49,180
数千名基督教徒被处以死刑
Thousands of Christians are executed.

475
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:57,800
他们就是人们所尊称的殉道者
They become known as martyrs.

476
00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:01,330
但是罗马人杀死的基督教徒越多
But the more Christians the Romans kill,

477
00:42:01,330 --> 00:42:05,570
基督教就越是盛行
The more popular the religion becomes.

478
00:42:05,570 --> 00:42:09,370
一百年间 基督教徒数量
In 100 years, the number of followers grows

479
00:42:09,370 --> 00:42:13,180
由二十万上升到六百万
from 200,000 to six million.

480
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:19,000
在罗马 每十人中就有一名基督教徒
1 in 10 people in the empire is Christian.

481
00:42:23,850 --> 00:42:26,020
