00:44:00,530 --> 00:44:03,290
政治上或者经济上的利益
politically and economically,

501
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:06,780
就需要成为基督教徒
needs to be a Christian as well.

502
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:17,520
新的基督教中心在帝国的东方崛起
A new Christian capital rises in the east of the empire:

503
00:44:17,520 --> 00:44:23,420
那就是君士坦丁堡 也就是现在的伊斯坦布尔
Constantinople, today Istanbul.

504
00:44:23,430 --> 00:44:29,760
城中心矗立着一座比罗马任何寺庙都大的教堂
At its heart, a church larger than any temple in Rome.

505
00:44:29,770 --> 00:44:35,420
圣索菲亚大教堂 圣神智慧的殿堂
Hagia Sophia, the church of the holy wisdom.

506
00:44:43,880 --> 00:44:48,450
今天 全球有二十二亿的基督教徒
Today there are 2.2 billion Christians,

507
00:44:48,450 --> 00:44:52,520
占世界总人口的三分之一
Nearly a third of the world's population.

508
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:55,690
基督的追随者们改变了世界的每一个地方
His followers have changed every part, every portion,

509
00:44:55,690 --> 00:44:57,760
每一个部分 每一个角落
every corner of the earth,

510
00:44:57,760 --> 00:45:01,090
这一切都归功于两千年前的这个人
and that has to be understood as the power of this one person

511
00:45:01,100 --> 00:45:04,460
所带来的力量
over 2,000 years ago.

512
00:45:05,260 --> 00:45:08,560
在中东 一个男人的死亡
One man's death in the Middle East

513
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:13,700
让一种新的讯息在世界各地广泛传播
Inspires a message that spreads around the world,

514
00:45:14,180 --> 00:45:17,420
世界从未像这般紧密相连
A world connected like never before.

515
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:30,280
基督教是罗马帝国留下的一笔永恒的遗产
Christianity, the lasting legacy of the Roman Empire.

516
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:37,720
但在帝国衰落后 我们重建自己的家园
But when empires fall, we remake our world.

517
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:46,530
我们不断创新 探索...
We innovate and explore...

518
00:45:46,530 --> 00:45:52,270
新的思想和机遇随之而来
New ideas, new opportunities.

519
00:45:52,270 --> 00:45:56,380
但同样 新的冲突也无可避免
But also new conflicts.

520
00:45:57,610 --> 00:46:02,610
这就是文明间的相互碰撞
A clash of civilizations.

